Subject: File Server Activity Import Failure
Description: File Server Activity appears to be failing to import into the database. I have included additional details in the comments of the ticket.
DevOps_Steps_to_Reproduce__c:
Open AIC
Select File system
Last scan shows as 2021
What_We_Know__c:
--------
03/14/2025
--------
Bulk import was hitting the error "Tier 2 database does not match Tier 1 data"
We ran the FSAA RESET maintenance task for the host and restarted bulk import. The bulk import appears to be working and we will wait to verify it completes.

--------
03/04/2025
--------
FSAA scan has been disabled and does not appear to have run since 2021.
We setup a new schedule to let it run overnight and will follow up tomorrow.
Next_Steps__c: Awaiting results of bulk import job.
Solution_Comment__c:
Issue:
AIC showing last scan was from 2021

Cause:
FSAA scans have been disabled and have not run since 2021.

Resolution:
We enabled the FSAA scan and set it up to run on a schedule. Cleared T2 database data to allow bulk import to proceed.
